modules.description: This module defines functions to register and execute inline Alcotest test cases. It works with test functions that take no arguments and return unit, organizing them under named paths. Use it to embed test suites directly within OCaml modules for lightweight, executable specifications.

This module implements inline test definitions and conditional code dropping based on location attributes. It transforms test expressions into module structures, supporting direct test placement within implementation files. Key operations include parsing test annotations, generating test code, and handling optional test execution through the `drop_mode` flag.
